items.abstract:
<jats:p>Let <jats:inline-formula>
                  <jats:alternatives>
                     <jats:inline-graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" mime-subtype="gif" xlink:href="S0010437X17007138_inline1" xlink:type="simple" />
                     <jats:tex-math>$M$</jats:tex-math>
                  </jats:alternatives>
               </jats:inline-formula> be an irreducible holomorphic symplectic (hyperkähler) manifold. If <jats:inline-formula>
                  <jats:alternatives>
                     <jats:inline-graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" mime-subtype="gif" xlink:href="S0010437X17007138_inline2" xlink:type="simple" />
                     <jats:tex-math>$b_{2}(M)\geqslant 5$</jats:tex-math>
                  </jats:alternatives>
               </jats:inline-formula>, we construct a deformation <jats:inline-formula>
                  <jats:alternatives>
                     <jats:inline-graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" mime-subtype="gif" xlink:href="S0010437X17007138_inline3" xlink:type="simple" />
                     <jats:tex-math>$M^{\prime }$</jats:tex-math>
                  </jats:alternatives>
               </jats:inline-formula> of <jats:inline-formula>
                  <jats:alternatives>
                     <jats:inline-graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" mime-subtype="gif" xlink:href="S0010437X17007138_inline4" xlink:type="simple" />
                     <jats:tex-math>$M$</jats:tex-math>
                  </jats:alternatives>
               </jats:inline-formula> which admits a symplectic automorphism of infinite order. This automorphism is hyperbolic, that is, its action on the space of real <jats:inline-formula>
                  <jats:alternatives>
                     <jats:inline-graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" mime-subtype="gif" xlink:href="S0010437X17007138_inline5" xlink:type="simple" />
                     <jats:tex-math>$(1,1)$</jats:tex-math>
                  </jats:alternatives>
               </jats:inline-formula>-classes is hyperbolic. If <jats:inline-formula>
                  <jats:alternatives>
                     <jats:inline-graphic xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" mime-subtype="gif" xlink:href="S0010437X17007138_inline6" xlink:type="simple" />
                     <jats:tex-math>$b_{2}(M)\geqslant 14$</jats:tex-math>
                  </jats:alternatives>
               </jats:inline-formula>, similarly, we construct a deformation which admits a parabolic automorphism (and many other automorphisms as well).</jats:p>
title: Construction of automorphisms of hyperkähler manifolds
